Methods
---------------------------------------

``setCookie(name, value, days, path, domain, secure)``:

``set(name, value, days, path, domain, secure)``:

    Sets a cookie.

    ``name``:
        Name of the cookie. This will be used when you want to retrieve your
        cookie later.

    ``value``:
        Value of the cookie. This will be the ``toString()`` of your passed
        ``value``.

    ``days``:
        Number of days to set the cookie for. Set to ``-1`` to create a session
        cookie.

    ``path``:
        Optional. Path of the cookie.

    ``domain``:
        Optional. Domain of the cookie.

    ``secure``:
        Optional. If true, denote the cookie as secure.

    *return*:
        null

``getCookie(name)``:

``get(name)``:

    Get a stored cookie's value.

    ``name``:
        Name of the cookie to retrieve.

    *return*:
        Value of the ``name``d cookie. If no cookie matches ``name``, returns
        null.

``setObjectCookie(name, obj, days, path, domain, secure, clearCurrent)``:

``setObjectCookie(name, obj, days, path, clearCurrent)``:

    Set a cookie with object/value pairs as the value instead of simple data
    type.

    ``name``:
        Name of the cookie. This will be used when you want to retrieve your
        cookie later.

    ``obj``:
        Object to store.

    ``days``:
        Number of days to set the cookie for. Set to ``-1`` to create a session
        cookie.

    ``path``:
        Optional. Path of the cookie.

    ``domain``:
        Optional. Domain of the cookie.

    ``secure``:
        Optional. If true, denote the cookie as secure.

    ``clearCurrent``:
        Optional. If true, ignores the current object cookie stored in ``name``.
        Otherwise, checks for cookie ``name`` to add/remove values to cookie.

    *return*:
        null

``getObjectCookie(name)``:

    Retrieves an object cookie's object.

    ``name``:
        Name of the cookie to retrieve.

    *return*:
        Object stored in cookie ``name``. If no cookie matches ``name``, returns
        null.

``isSupported()``:

    Checks to see if the browser supports and allows cookies.

    *return*:
        True if supported and allowed, false otherwise.

